<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000844/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """The course will be passed if a grade of at least 5 out of a total of 10 points is obtained, provided that the minimum grade is achieved in activities with a required minimum. If this minimum is not achieved, the grade cannot be higher than 4.5.
The evaluation assesses whether the students have acquired all the course competencies. The global and extraordinary evaluations will use the same evaluation techniques as the progressive evaluation and will take place on the dates and times approved by the School Council (Junta de Escuela) for the current academic year. However, activities that assess learning outcomes that cannot be evaluated through a final exam will take place throughout the semester.
Specifically, the evaluation will include a written group work and an oral presentation of the work. This activity is mandatory and non-recoverable, since the work must be presented publicly to all the students, and everyone must participate in the subsequent debate (competence CG4). After each group's oral presentation, a debate will be initiated, during which students must demonstrate their understanding of all aspects of the work presented. This activity will take place during weeks 13 and 14, depending on the number of presentations. The exact dates of the presentations will be announced at least 14 days in advance.
Progressive evaluation:
This is the recommended method. It includes:
Participation and exercises during the classes (10%)
First partial exam (35%)
Second partial exam (35%)
Teamwork: Written text and oral presentation of a case study selected by teams of two students (20%)
Global exam
To take the final exam, students must have previously presented the written and oral teamwork assignments with the same rules and dates as the progressive evaluation.
The global exam will cover the entire course syllabus. Students must submit a written request to take the exam at least two weeks before the scheduled date.
Extraordinary (re-sit) assessment
To take the final exam, students must have previously presented the written and oral teamwork assignments with the same rules and dates as the progressive evaluation.
This exam will cover the entire course syllabus."""@es ;
